		<!-- message -->
		<div>I agree with the quote in the original post.  Class balance as it is currently cannot be achieved, simply because if you balance one class against the others, something changes, and throws the rest out of balance again.  Those players will kick up a fuss, which will get their class changed, or another nerfed, which repeats the cycle.<br />
<br />
Class vs Class balancing is a pointless waste of time.<br />
<br />
Class vs Environment balancing is much better.  You fight the common enemy (players vs the monsters) and not each other (class vs class).  By this definition, the most balanced classes are probably necros, bards, and druids.  They are best able to combat the majority of the environment with a variety of similar methods.  <br />
<br />
Just my 2cp.<br />
<br />
~Eli</div>
